status.description: A resolution has been taken, and it is awaiting verification by reporter. From here issues are either reopened, or are closed.

comments.comment:
The failure is caused by a new feature of IBM JDK8 - class and classloader caching in ObjectInputStram. Disabling the cache (-Dcom.ibm.enableClassCaching=false) makes the test pass. If the caching is enabled JDK also caches classloder used for object resolution within SerialCallbackContext which seems to trigger the failure. I don't think there is much we can do besides adding deps to all required internal modules to the deployments.

As there is a workaround (-Dcom.ibm.enableClassCaching=false) I would suggest to close the issue.

Hi Dominik,
this doesn't work for me. Tested with WF master and latest IBM8 and the test still fails even if I add -Dcom.ibm.enableClassCaching=false. Also, according to documentation, "The default value for this property is false.".

Which java version are you using? In IBM JDK version I am using it defaults to true. Please have a look ObjectInputStream.java in src.zip. Mine has:

String property = System.getProperty("com.ibm.enableClassCaching", "true");

Are you setting the property properly on server side?

I wanted to avoid any interaction with other tests, but if that it's a prefered way I can update the PR.

e.g. adding the following profile into testsuite/integration/web/pom.xml solves the issue as well

        <profile>
 
            <id>ibmjdk.profile</id>
 
            <activation>
 
                <property>
 
                    <name>java.vendor</name>
 
                    <value>IBM Corporation</value>
 
                </property>
 
            </activation>
 
            <build>
 
                <plugins>
 
                    <plugin>
 
                        <groupId>org.apache.maven.plugins</groupId>
 
                        <artifactId>maven-surefire-plugin</artifactId>
 
                        <configuration>
 
                            <systemPropertyVariables>
 
                                <jboss.args>${jboss.args} -Dcom.ibm.enableClassCaching=false</jboss.args>
 
                            </systemPropertyVariables>
 
                        </configuration>
 
                    </plugin>
 
                </plugins>
 
            </build>
 
        </profile>

or I can simply update the systemPropertyVariables in surefire configuration of web module. Just let me know.
Updated PR, previous works only if the test was started by -Dtest option.
